race.comment: Siding with KINGSLEY TOWN (3) in this event despite a lacklustre debut as a 50-1 shot. That was in far stronger company however and the blinkers go on for the first time today. This shapes as a much better assignment now and he can turn his form right around. LONGTIMEBELIEVER (6) was very good at Narrogin first-up on the back of a Lark Hill trial win coming in. The wide draw is a niggle, though she does have plenty of early speed and if she can run up to the first-up effort, then she'll be very hard to beat. SATIN BOW (11) fell at Kalgoorlie at her last start in April, though her two trials coming into this have been very impressive. She looks well placed off those trials and she can storm over the top of her rivals. TRADED MY SHOES (9) is not to be discounted coming back to Country level. MANTA RAY BAY (5) was good from the back here 30 days ago and is not out of this.
